<p>Is it possible to have different sized (i.e. thick) lines drawn with <code>geom_line</code>?</p>  <p>The size parameters is the same for all lines, irrespective of the group:</p>  <pre><code>bp &lt;- ggplot(data=diamonds, aes(x=cut, y=depth)) +   geom_line(aes(color=cut), size=1) </code></pre>  <p>However, I want the thickness of the lines to reflect their relative importance measured as number of observations:</p>  <pre><code>relative_size &lt;- table(diamonds$cut)/nrow(diamonds) bp &lt;- ggplot(data=diamonds, aes(x=cut, y=depth)) +   geom_line(aes(color=cut), size=cut) bp # Error: Incompatible lengths for set aesthetics: size </code></pre>  <p>Interestingly, <code>geom_line(..., size=cut)</code> works but not as expected, since it doesn't alter line size at all.</p>